      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ORDASHUS (2) tackled stronger races last campaign where he was just outclassed. Now lines up for the new stable and on his home deck and hasn't been sighted since his last start at Pinjarra. Finds a very suitable race on that form however and he can return with a win. COSTA STAR (6) improved last time out, finishing 1.2 lengths from the winner in second at the end of 1200m at this track after being prominent at the bend. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. ALL KING'S (4) is fitter for two runs back from a spell, progressing nicely last time to finish third, beaten 4.5 lengths, at this track over 1200m. Blinkers are removed. Should run well. WILLYABRUP (3) was prominent until they straightened last time but weakened to finish sixth, beaten 12 lengths, over 2200m at Northam. This looks a nice race so expect him to finish closer. AL'S GAL (9) is next best.",
